{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7e3f731f-a464-491f-8fde-7989d92a1951","content":"**Exit code 8** in Microsoft.Testing.Platform means \"no tests were found.\" By default MTP expects at least 1 test per assembly — unlike VSTest, which silently succeeded with zero.\n\n**Fix:** The added `TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments` property passes `--minimum-expected-tests 0` to the test runner, telling it that zero discovered tests is acceptable (exit 0 instead of 8).\n\nYou can also pass this at the CLI level instead:\n```\ndotnet test -- --minimum-expected-tests 0\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ab89b508-1dc4-4205-919c-99e925f6c006","outputTokens":128,"requestId":"5C25:19AB05:D3B78:10678C:69F54C02"},"id":"963a6e2c-afb4-41e5-b5b0-26fc8782e763","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:57:43.296Z","parentId":"dc161c5b-470e-43b8-9150-16692e33ff2a"}
